<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="3" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[189,1399,1359,1981]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Species of the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[569,644,1359,1383]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Seseli" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[569,644,1359,1383]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Seseli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. (
<taxonomicName box="[698,814,1359,1383]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Apiaceae</taxonomicName>
) are most commonly cited as host plants of 
<taxonomicName box="[189,314,1396,1420]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Phytoecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argus">
<emphasis box="[189,314,1396,1420]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Ph. argus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Bense" box="[333,492,1396,1421]" firstAuthor="Bense" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" refId="ref1173" refString="Bense, U. (1995) Longhorn Beetles. Illustrated key to the Cerambycidae and Vesperidae of Europe. Margraf Verlag, 512 pp." type="book" year="1995">Bense 1995</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Rejzek" box="[508,751,1396,1421]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Rejzek" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="263 - 294" refId="ref1656" refString="Rejzek, M., Sama, G. &amp; Alziar, G. (2001) Host plants of several herb-feeding Cerambycidae mainly from east Mediterranean region (Coleoptera: Cerambycidae). Biocosme mesogeen, 17 (4): 263 - 294." type="journal article" year="2001">
Rejzek 
<emphasis box="[604,669,1396,1420]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">et al.</emphasis>
2001
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Sama" box="[766,921,1397,1421]" firstAuthor="Sama" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" refId="ref1702" refString="Sama, G. (2002) Atlas of the Cerambycidae of Europe and the Mediterranean Area. Vol. 1. Northern, Western, Central and Eastern Europe, British Isles and Continental Europe from France (excluding Corsica) to Scandinavia and Urals. Nakladatelstvi Kabourek, Zlin, 173 pp." type="book" year="2002">Sama 2002</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Migliaccio" box="[937,1224,1396,1421]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Migliaccio" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="1 - 78" refId="ref1515" refString="Migliaccio, E., Georgiev, G. &amp; Gashtarov, V. (2007) An annotated list of Bulgarian Cerambycids with special view on the rarest species and endemics (Coleoptera: Cerambycidae). Lambillionea, 107 (1), Supplement 1: 1 - 78" type="journal article" year="2007">
Migliaccio 
<emphasis box="[1078,1143,1396,1420]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">et al.</emphasis>
2007
</bibRefCitation>
, Hoskovec 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">et al.</emphasis>
2019). Known host plants of 
<taxonomicName box="[653,728,1434,1458]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Seseli" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[653,728,1434,1458]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Seseli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
genus are summarized by 
<bibRefCitation author="Rejzek" box="[1120,1394,1434,1458]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Rejzek" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="263 - 294" refId="ref1656" refString="Rejzek, M., Sama, G. &amp; Alziar, G. (2001) Host plants of several herb-feeding Cerambycidae mainly from east Mediterranean region (Coleoptera: Cerambycidae). Biocosme mesogeen, 17 (4): 263 - 294." type="journal article" year="2001">
Rejzek 
<emphasis box="[1221,1291,1434,1458]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">et al.</emphasis>
(2001)
</bibRefCitation>
, including the following species – 
<taxonomicName authority="Besser" authorityName="Besser" authorityYear="1816" box="[633,861,1471,1495]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Seseli" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pallasii">
<emphasis box="[633,762,1471,1495]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">S. pallasii</emphasis>
Besser
</taxonomicName>
(syn. 
<taxonomicName authority="Trev." authorityName="Trev." box="[946,1150,1472,1496]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Seseli" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="varium">
<emphasis box="[946,1071,1472,1495]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">S. varium</emphasis>
Trev.
</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName box="[1175,1318,1472,1495]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Seseli" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="annuum">
<emphasis box="[1175,1318,1472,1495]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">S. annuum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L., 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Arcangeli" authorityYear="1882" baseAuthorityName="Rchb. fil." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Seseli" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="montanum" subSpecies="tommasinii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">S. montanum</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis box="[446,586,1509,1532]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">tommasinii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Rchb. f.) (syn. 
<taxonomicName authority="Rchb." authorityName="Rchb." box="[824,1097,1508,1532]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Seseli" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tommasinii">
<emphasis box="[824,1005,1509,1532]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">S. tommasinii</emphasis>
Rchb.
</taxonomicName>
f.) and 
<taxonomicName authority="Simonk. Along" authorityName="Simonk. Along" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Seseli" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="devenyense">
<emphasis box="[1206,1399,1508,1532]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">S. devenyense</emphasis>
Simonk. Along
</taxonomicName>
with this more accepted view, 
<bibRefCitation author="Zettel" box="[787,952,1546,1570]" firstAuthor="Zettel" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="159 - 161" refId="ref1973" refString="Zettel, H. (2006) Ein neuer Fund von Musaria argus (Frolich, 1793) (Coleoptera: Cerambycidae) von den Hainburger Bergen, Niederosterreich. Beitrage zur Entomofaunistik, 7: 159 - 161." type="journal article" year="2006">Zettel (2006)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Merkl &amp; Szel" box="[1020,1279,1546,1570]" firstAuthor="Merkl" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="373 - 458" refId="ref1458" refString="Merkl, O. &amp; Szel, G. (2012) A Sas-hegy bogarfaunaja (Coleoptera). In: Kezdy P. &amp; Toth Z. (Eds), Termeszetvedelem es kutatas a budai Sas- hegyen. Rosalia tanulmanykotetek 8. Duna-Ipoly Nemzeti Park Igazgatosag, Budapest, pp. 373 - 458." type="book chapter" year="2012">Merkl &amp; Szél (2012)</bibRefCitation>
reported a relationship of 
<taxonomicName box="[419,544,1583,1607]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Phytoecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argus">
<emphasis box="[419,544,1583,1607]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Ph. argus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also with 
<taxonomicName box="[688,807,1583,1607]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Trinia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glauca">
<emphasis box="[688,807,1583,1607]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">T. glauca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the same plant family for 
<collectingCountry box="[1242,1338,1583,1607]" name="Austria" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Austria</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[189,306,1621,1645]" name="Hungary" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Hungary</collectingCountry>
, respectively. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Merkl &amp; Szel" box="[673,944,1621,1645]" firstAuthor="Merkl" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="373 - 458" refId="ref1458" refString="Merkl, O. &amp; Szel, G. (2012) A Sas-hegy bogarfaunaja (Coleoptera). In: Kezdy P. &amp; Toth Z. (Eds), Termeszetvedelem es kutatas a budai Sas- hegyen. Rosalia tanulmanykotetek 8. Duna-Ipoly Nemzeti Park Igazgatosag, Budapest, pp. 373 - 458." type="book chapter" year="2012">Merkl &amp; Szél (2012)</bibRefCitation>
, beetles can be found as early as April at the base of both 
<taxonomicName authority="Hoffm." authorityName="Hoffm." box="[524,696,1658,1682]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Trinia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[524,598,1659,1682]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Trinia</emphasis>
Hoffm.
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[766,841,1658,1682]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Seseli" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[766,841,1658,1682]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Seseli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
host plants. Adult beetles are active from April to June and the larval development is at the roots of both 
<taxonomicName box="[1063,1182,1695,1719]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Trinia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glauca">
<emphasis box="[1063,1182,1695,1719]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">T. glauca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1256,1331,1695,1719]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Seseli" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1256,1331,1695,1719]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Seseli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. (
<bibRefCitation author="Merkl &amp; Szel" box="[197,442,1733,1757]" firstAuthor="Merkl" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="373 - 458" refId="ref1458" refString="Merkl, O. &amp; Szel, G. (2012) A Sas-hegy bogarfaunaja (Coleoptera). In: Kezdy P. &amp; Toth Z. (Eds), Termeszetvedelem es kutatas a budai Sas- hegyen. Rosalia tanulmanykotetek 8. Duna-Ipoly Nemzeti Park Igazgatosag, Budapest, pp. 373 - 458." type="book chapter" year="2012">Merkl &amp; Szél 2012</bibRefCitation>
). Our record seems to confirm the ability of 
<taxonomicName box="[1022,1145,1733,1757]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Phytoecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argus">
<emphasis box="[1022,1145,1733,1757]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Ph. argus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to use 
<taxonomicName box="[1243,1359,1733,1757]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Trinia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glauca">
<emphasis box="[1243,1359,1733,1757]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">T. glauca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a host plant as well.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[189,1399,1359,1981]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
The distribution of 
<taxonomicName box="[557,686,1807,1831]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Phytoecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argus">
<emphasis box="[557,686,1807,1831]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Ph. argus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
seems to be restricted to the remnants of natural steppe habitats in the Western Palaearctic (
<bibRefCitation author="Schoppmann" box="[769,1022,1845,1869]" firstAuthor="Schoppmann" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="113 - 125" refId="ref1843" refString="Schoppmann, A. (1990) Faunistik der Cerambyciden aus der Umgebung von Wien und vom Bisamberg. Zeitschrift der Arbeitsgemeinschaft Osterreichischer Entomologen, 41 (3 / 4): 113 - 125." type="journal article" year="1990">Schoppmann 1990</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Pokorny" box="[1038,1224,1844,1869]" firstAuthor="Pokorny" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="11 - 21" refId="ref1625" refString="Pokorny, P. (2005) Novy prirustek do entomologickych sbirek Regionalniho muzea v Mikulove. RegioM. Sbornik Regionalniho muzea v Mikulove, 2005: 11 - 21." type="journal article" year="2005">Pokorný 2005</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Zettel" box="[1240,1393,1845,1869]" firstAuthor="Zettel" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="159 - 161" refId="ref1973" refString="Zettel, H. (2006) Ein neuer Fund von Musaria argus (Frolich, 1793) (Coleoptera: Cerambycidae) von den Hainburger Bergen, Niederosterreich. Beitrage zur Entomofaunistik, 7: 159 - 161." type="journal article" year="2006">Zettel 2006</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Merkl" box="[189,348,1882,1907]" firstAuthor="Merkl" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="295 - 322" refId="ref1427" refString="Merkl, O. (2008) Adatok a Szenas- hegycsoport bogarfaunajahoz (Coleoptera). Termeszetvedelem es kutatas a Szenas- hegycsoporton. Rosalia, 4: 295 - 322." type="journal article" year="2008">Merkl 2008</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Shapovalov" box="[368,602,1882,1907]" firstAuthor="Shapovalov" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="1 - 10" refId="ref1793" refString="Shapovalov, A. M. (2012) The peculiarities of zoogeographic structure of the fauna of longicorn beetles (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae) of the Orenburg region. Bulleten' Orenburgskogo naucnogo centra UrO RAN, 4: 1 - 10 (in Russian, English summary)." type="journal article" year="2012">Shapovalov 2012</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Dedyukhin" box="[621,849,1882,1906]" firstAuthor="Dedyukhin" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="124 - 143" refId="ref1286" refString="Dedyukhin, S. V. (2016) Relict elements fauna of the phytophagous beetles (Coleoptera, Chrysomelidae, Curculionoidea) of the east of the Russian Plain and their natural refuges. Bulletin of Perm University. Biology, 2016 (2): 124 - 143 (in Russian, English summary)." type="journal article" year="2016">Dedyukhin 2016</bibRefCitation>
). We conclude that the species may be useful as an indicator species for the assessment of the conservation status of natural steppe habitats in Europe.
</paragraph>
